### Implementation

#### Files Created:

1. **crates/worker/src/agent_executor.rs** (409 lines)
   - `AgentRunConfig` struct: agent_cli, agent_token, prompt, prompt_context, work_dir, model, sentinel
   - `AgentOutput` struct: exit_code, stdout, stderr, assistant_reply, sentinel_found (with Default derive)
   - `find_agent_cli(agent_cli: &AgentCli) -> Result<PathBuf>` - uses `which` crate to search PATH
   - `run_agent(config, client, task_id, platform) -> Result<AgentOutput>` - main execution function:
     - Finds CLI binary on PATH
     - Builds full prompt (prepends persona context if provided)
     - Builds command via platform handler
     - Sets auth env vars via platform handler
     - Spawns subprocess with piped stdout/stderr, null stdin
     - Reads stdout and stderr concurrently via tokio::spawn
     - Waits for subprocess exit
     - Sends completion log entry to control plane
   - `process_stdout(stdout, sentinel, client, task_id)` - async stdout processing:
     - Line-by-line reading via BufReader
     - Parses stream-json format for assistant reply text
     - Detects sentinel substring
     - Buffers log entries, flushes to control plane every 2 seconds
   - `process_stderr(stderr)` - async stderr collection
   - `parse_stream_json_line(line: &str) -> Option<String>` - parses Claude Code stream-json:
     - "assistant" type: extracts text from message.content blocks
     - "content_block_delta" type: extracts text_delta text
     - "result" type with subtype "text": extracts result text
   - `detect_sentinel(text, sentinel)` - case-sensitive substring check
   - 12 unit tests covering: CLI discovery error, all stream-json parsing variants, sentinel detection, AgentOutput default, AgentRunConfig with persona

2. **crates/worker/src/platform/mod.rs** (131 lines)
   - `PlatformHandler` trait: build_command(), set_env(), platform_name()
